{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"716b6272-9056-4d51-8ff6-7af3c7091c2f","content":"There's no repo-specific guidance here, but here's how to migrate:\n\n## Key changes\n\n**1. Replace `VSTest@3` with `dotnet test`** using the `DotNetCoreCLI@2` task (or a plain script). Microsoft.Testing.Platform runs via `dotnet test` — no VSTest adapter needed.\n\n**2. Enable the new platform** in your `.csproj`:\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**3. Update your pipeline** — replace the VSTest task:\n\n```yaml\n# Before\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**\\*Tests.dll'\n    resultsFolder: $(Agent.TempDirectory)\\TestResults\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n\n# After\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish test results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n**4. For Cobertura format** (recommended for `PublishCodeCoverageResults@2`), add the `coverlet.collector` NuGet package and use:\n```\n--collect \"XPlat Code Coverage\"\n```\n\nThe key difference: VSTest@3 auto-publishes results; with `dotnet test` you must explicitly add `PublishTestResults@2` and `PublishCodeCoverageResults@2` tasks.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"df7c99b0-6fa5-42e9-ba0b-3f8fb735f47b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repository doesn't have specific content about this migration. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge of migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps pipelines.","outputTokens":587,"requestId":"0433:3FE43:1F88B83:2357C81:69E81A63"},"id":"2f567111-f23b-402c-b0fe-89ab9e4cbc5a","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:46:38.260Z","parentId":"a15901d2-ae50-4788-a28b-eb5102c3bf13"}
